      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Since this question is coming up in a bunch of different threads, let me address this specific item here.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The Cloak of the Spirit Tracker was built after the initial implementation of evolving items and used a much lower amount of experience required to level it up than normal evolving items.&amp;nbsp; This was to make it level at a rate closer to what we originally envisioned for evolving items than at&amp;nbsp;the slow rate they were actually levelling at.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;In an effort to improve the overall time it takes to evolve all items, with this patch we significantly improved the amount of experience you gain toward an evolving item&amp;nbsp;when you get a kill.&amp;nbsp; This in turn&amp;nbsp;caused the Cloak to&amp;nbsp; level up way too fast.&amp;nbsp; To correct this, we had to increase the amount of experience the Cloak requires to level so it is more in line with other evolving items, which should now level up at a much more appropriate rate.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;If you had a cloak before this patch, after the patch it still has the same amount of XP in it that it had before the patch.&amp;nbsp; No XP has been lost or removed from the item.&amp;nbsp; The cloak does, though, require more experience to level up now than it did before, so the experience you had in it is a lower percent of the total experience than before the change.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;This means the Cloak will display a lower percent toward the next level than it did before the patch even though the amount of experience it has is the same.&amp;nbsp; In addition,&amp;nbsp;if it was borderline between levels, it may&amp;nbsp;devolve a level since it no longer has enough experience to reach level 2 or 3.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
