    <item>
      <title>Re: Cloak of the Spirit Tracker</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=242187#M242187</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;As some one who was affected both by the roll backs and the recent cloak de leveling I will have to say that I was much more upset over the rollbacks then sony's most recent screw up.&amp;nbsp; I was relatively lucky with the roll backs in that the only thing that I actually lost was one PoP flag and one item that I picked up on that raid,neither made or broke my character.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;In the case of the rollbacks however I could see the need for them as items from an as yet unreleased expansion had made it to the live servers, really no way that you could expect SoE to let that fly, Did they go about taking care of it the right way? a resounding no, was some action necessary? yes&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Now to the current situation, I had obtained my cloak about&amp;nbsp; 4 days prior to the patch, I had it leveled to somewhere around 40% on level 2, most of this I got the same way I had leveled my blade of the ecplipse, soloing in GE, the rate of exp increase for both of these items was about the same, was 2 kills per % on the cloak and 2 or 3 per % on the blade, I had previously done some work on a twisted shank and found it to be about the same in GE.&amp;nbsp; The only reason that the cloak leveled so much faster in terms of reaching the final stage is that it has significantly fewer stanges then the other two, the rate of exp increase was about the same.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Enter the current situation, After my cloak deleveled I decided that I would go and try to recover the lost exp, as Veksar was the new hot zone and its dificulty was about on par with GE I decided to go there to exp, 8 kills later I got a % and decided to give it up in frustration, Later that night I was grouping in MPG for about an hour, didn't even make a percent and I know I killed more then 8 mobs, so my question is where is this mythical grouping bonus? while all the mobs were blue they were all obviously significantly higher level then the ones in veksar and yet my cloak did not advance at all? I realize that on some of the more difficult to evolve intelligent items that the situation has been grately improved, all well and good, I have an evolving bow that I am going to be attempting to level here shortly and am looking forward to it going faster, but again it doesn't particularily help the situation at the moment.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Was the cloak too easy to level? probably. Was there a need to slow it down? maybe, difficult to say as I don't see it leveling any where close to the old rate and on all the other non intelligent items I have worked with rate seemed about fine, was only the total amount that was annoying.&amp;nbsp; Should they have de leveled peoples cloaks in order to fit it into some concept on how fast the items should take to evolve and then not have it conform to that? No.&amp;nbsp; While I am not going to quit over this, have already invested far to much time and effort into my characters to do that, it does go on the pile of increasing disatisfaction with EQ as a whole.&amp;nbsp; Am still upset with them over not being to renew at the $99 rate because we changed banks but that is a different issue entierly.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Once again way to upset your player base, unfortunatly for me will just have to bend over and take it like everything else.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Oh on a side note if your cloak displays a negative % and is still level two it will de level with your next kill, thats what happened with mine at least, I suspect that if you turn exp to the item off you could maintain it at level 2 but with no hope of ever getting it to level 3.&amp;nbsp; And no this doesn't warrant a double exp weekend.. unless they decide to make that exp only apply towards evolving item exp ;)&lt;/P&gt;</description>
